stimates of the frequency of Earth-like planets and\nan increase of 26% (4.5 $\\sigma$) for super-Earths and sub-Neptunes. These\noccurrence increases are not entirely commensurate with theoretical\npredictions, though this discrepancy may be due to differences in the treatment\nof stellar binarity.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 18 Nov 2020 22:25:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-12-02"}
