apability\nfor space-based, high-energy cosmic neutrino detection. Specifically, we show\nthat for neutrino energies $\\lt$ 10 PeV, the upward-EAS sensitivity due to muon\nneutrino interactions in the Earth begin to dominate over that for tau neutrino\ninteractions, effectively extending the neutrino sensitivity to lower energies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 19 Nov 2020 14:49:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-03-03"}
